{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7dbef554-3768-4011-935c-7dbb5c309827","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n**In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Replace** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` with the unified `MSTest` v3 NuGet package (it bundles the test SDK, framework, and adapter)\n\n**In `OrderServiceTests.cs`:** No changes needed — MSTest v3 keeps the same `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace and attributes.\n\nWant me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_F7UG30iyx043lLCyBMFYbU","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-1a709a7fe85745f9a90602e8adb82ea9/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-1a709a7fe85745f9a90602e8adb82ea9/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"19ba78d7-0c7a-47e2-b72a-77eefd392dd9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to upgrade from the old MSTest (via assembly reference) to MSTest v3. Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove the old assembly reference** to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add the MSTest v3 NuGet package** - MSTest v3 consolidated everything into a single `MSTest` package (replacing the old `MSTest.TestAdapter` + `MSTest.TestFramework` combo)\n3. **Update `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** to a newer version (or it may be pulled transitively)\n\n\n4. The target framework should be fine as-is since MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above, and the namespace stays the same. The `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` dependency might actually be handled transitively now with the consolidated package.\n\nSo the migration really comes down to swapping out the old reference for the new `MSTest` meta-package—I'll remove the direct QualityTools reference and replace the Test.Sdk package with MSTest v3, probably around version 3.6 or 3.7 depending on what's current. The test code itself shouldn't need any changes since backward compatibility is maintained.","outputTokens":990,"requestId":"EC0A:1B7339:631EF35:6BA08AF:6A034B80"},"id":"ede8b4ee-1893-451c-a8d0-9b0f4e4f1169","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:47:30.040Z","parentId":"75fe084e-d93f-42b2-9bdf-ec102997b818"}
